‚ö†Ô∏è Key Considerations
‚Ä¢ 	Interconnectedness: Credit and liquidity risks are often linked‚Äîdefaults reduce liquidity, while liquidity shortages increase credit risk.
‚Ä¢ 	Quantification Challenge: Legal risk is hardest to measure; firms rely on qualitative assessments and provisioning.
‚Ä¢ 	Best Practice: Combine quantitative models (for credit/liquidity) with qualitative frameworks (for legal) to build a holistic risk management strategy.
